Here are the MSTest attributes/patterns for each case:

**1. Windows-only (platform filter):**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)] // custom attribute, or:
public void RegistryTest()
{
    if (!RuntimeInformation.IsOSPlatform(OSPlatform.Windows))
        Assert.Inconclusive("Windows only");
    // ...
}
```

**2. Skip in CI (environment-based):**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void GpuTest()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU");
    // ...
}
```
Then in CI: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

**3. Flaky external API (retry with `[DataRow]` or custom logic):**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Timeout(10000)]
public void WeatherApiTest()
{
    Exception last = null;
    for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)
    {
        try
        {
            // call weather API and assert
            return; // success
        }
        catch (Exception ex) { last = ex; Thread.Sleep(1000); }
    }
    Assert.Fail($"Failed after 3 retries: {last?.Message}");
}
```
Or use a custom `[RetryAttribute]` (MSTest v3+ supports `[Retry(3)]` natively).

**4. Cleanup even on failure — use `[TestCleanup]`:**
```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string _tempFile;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup() =>
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();

    [TestMethod]
    public void WriteTempFileTest()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "data");
        Assert.IsTrue(File.Exists(_tempFile));
    }

    [TestCleanup] // runs even if the test fails
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }
}
```

**Summary table:**

| Scenario | Approach |
|---|---|
| OS-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` guard or custom attribute |
| Skip in CI | `[TestCategory]` + `--filter` + env-var guard |
| Flaky API | `[Retry(3)]` (MSTest v3+) or manual retry loop |
| Cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` — guaranteed to run after each test |
